    "However, the \"Industry\" category has relatively lower accuracy, only 93%.",
    "This could be due to the similar spatial distribution of industry in the \"industry\" category, leading to the loss of classification accuracy by the interference of these similar features.",
    "Table 2 shows the results of our proposed method compared with four state-of-the-art remote sensing image scene classification approaches on the PatternNet dataset.",
    "As clear from Table 2, the overall classification accuracy of our proposed method is 99% on the PatternNet test dataset, which is 7%, 4%, 4%, and 2% higher than that of multitask learning network (MTLN), error-tolerant deep learning (ETDL), Extracting Hierarchical and Collaborative intertarget feature Alignment (EHACA),and VGG-16, respectively.As shown in Fig. 9, it is asserted that the proposed strategy achieves satisfactory accuracy which attains 97% accuracy in 38 categories, and most categories obtain more than 98% accuracy.",
